Commentary Text: Green to Shubman Gill, 1 run, exhilarating century! "Shubman Gilling Mumbai," says Saurabh Shankar my colleague. After scoring 94* vs LSG at this venue, he was asked if he felt bad on missing a ton. This is what he said, "We have five more games and I will get my chance." And, he's got back-to-back hundreds here in Ahmedabad after that. Special knock by a special player in a big match! This is also his third century in four innings. Reaches there by knocking a length ball down to long-on. Punches the air, jumps in delight and then off comes the helmet...

Commentary Text: Shami to Nehal Wadhera, out Caught by Saha!! FOUR and OUT! Shami, unsurprisingly, strikes early. 139.6kph, seam-up ball, on a length and angled across the left-hander, Nehal Wadhera shapes up to pull it away and nicks off to the keeper.
